summary:
Jeroen Swinkels has over 15 years of experience in Research and Conservation Projects in the field of Biodiversity, Habitat and Species Conservation and Monitoring Assignments. He has also 15 years of experience in Academic Education Programs. He has been engaged both in long term and short-term assignments in Europe, South America, the Caribbean and Africa.
His project assignments encompassed Project Management, Project Coordination, Field Research, Capacity Development, Awareness Programs, (Technical) Reporting and Desk Studies. His dedicated and driven working ethic is characterized by the input of a broad array of technical research skills, an up to date knowledge of Biodiversity, Ecology and Conservation Issues and the flexibility to work under demanding conditions. As a strong team player, Jeroen is particularly capable of motivating colleagues and instigating new initiatives. He has strong organisational skills and is well practiced in people management.
Next to his project work, Jeroen has been engaged in Academic Education. His experience covers developing, coordinating and teaching practical courses for Bachelor students in Biology, Biomedical Sciences and Psychobiology. Jeroen has worked for Universities, NGOs, CBOs and public sector Ministries Departments and Agencies in multi- or bilateral affiliations, as well as freelancer.
